3 STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Secretary of the Senate.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 247, L.D. 567, “An Act to Designate the
10 2nd Week of May as Dark Sky Week”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Designate the 2nd Week of May and the 2nd Week of September as Dark
13 Sky Week'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 1 MRSA §150-W is enacted to read:
17 §150-W. Dark Sky Week
18 The 2nd full week in May and the 2nd full week in September of each year is designated
19 as Dark Sky Week to celebrate the dark skies of the State and to bring attention to the
20 effects of artificial light on spring bird migration and the importance of curbing artificial
21 light pollution. The Governor shall issue annually a proclamation inviting and urging
22 citizens and schools to observe each week with appropriate activities and study.'
23 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
24 number to read consecutively.
25 SUMMARY
2266 This amendment adds the 2nd full week in September of each year as an additional
2277 Dark Sky Week and changes the title.
2288 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2299 (See attached)
